Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, seeded, and thinly sliced into strips) into strips. Trim @scallions{4}(trimmed) and cut crosswise into ½-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper, @edamame{4%oz}, and scallions; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Rinse shrimp under cold water. Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with paper towels and season with salt and pepper. Add shrimp or chicken to pan along with veggies; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @pho stock concentrate{1}, @sriracha{1%tsp}, 1/4 cup water, and @brown sugar{1%tbsp} (be sure to measure—we sent more!). (For 4 servings, use ½ cup water and 2 tsp brown sugar.)

Once water is boiling, add @ramen noodles{4.5%oz} to pot. Cook until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Drain and rinse noodles under cold water, ~{30%seconds}.

Add another drizzle of @cooking oil{} to pan with veggies. Add @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add sauce mixture and drained noodles; toss to combine. Cook, tossing occasionally, until everything is coated in sauce, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Divide stir-fry between plates. Serve.